Google has created the "Android Open Source Development" (AOSD) / ["Android Open Source Project" (AOSP)|https://source.android.com/] which utilizes the tool ["Repo"|https://gerrit.googlesource.com/git-repo/+/refs/heads/master/README.md] for managing repositories which goes beyond just the abilities of Git.
{quote}
"Repo" is a tool built on top of Git. Repo helps manage many Git repositories, does the uploads to revision control systems, and automates parts of the development workflow. Repo is not meant to replace Git, only to make it easier to work with Git. The repo command is an executable Python script that you can put anywhere in your path.
{quote}
(i) [Additional details regarding Repo|https://source.android.com/setup/develop]
